Deputy President William Ruto has once again maintained any changes to the constitution must be  beneficial to the  general public and not a cross section of the political elite.
Ruto says the current debate  should focus on service delivery and how best to realise tangible development,
However a section of leaders have welcomed the referendum push but warned that the Independent Electoral And Boundaries Commission IEBC should first be reconstituted.
This as President Uhuru Kenyatta  called on leaders to stop politicking  and focus on service delivery.  